General.Name: Scandinavian ChemoTech AB Series B
General.Description: Scandinavian ChemoTech AB (publ) offers cancer care and pain management solutions. Its product, IQWave, is an electroporation device, used for treating head and neck squamous cell carcinoma, malignant melanoma, basal cell carcinoma, adenocarcinoma of the breast and salivary gland, hypernephroma, kaposi sarcoma, and transitional cell carcinoma. It also offers Vetiqure, a tumor specific electroporation used for treating solid and superficial malignant tumors for animals. The company markets its products through distribution channels and a network of opinion leaders in Middle East, Asia, India, Africa, and internationally. Scandinavian ChemoTech AB (publ) was incorporated in 2013 and is headquartered in Lund, Sweden.
